The article commends the Libyan Political Dialogue Forum (LPDF) for meeting in Geneva to finalize preparations for national elections in Libya on December 24, 2021. The United States expresses full support for these elections, which will allow Libyans to choose their own leaders and regain sovereignty after years of conflict and economic turmoil. The establishment of the interim Government of National Unity has also been seen as progress. The United States is encouraged by the positive atmosphere and spirit of compromise at the LPDF meetings, which are facilitated by the United Nations. The article emphasizes support for the Libyan people as they work towards a more stable, prosperous, and secure future.